{"data":{"post":{"id":"fa46e2ef-6f80-5967-b7b3-0006c4a64543","html":"<h3>Here’s what we are going to make</h3>\n<p><img src=\"/door_with_circular_drive-72d429b9aabde63e5fca5c5c8a674663.gif\" alt=\"Handpose with card\"></p>\n<h4>Let’s get started</h4>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<p>Download and install SteamVR into Unity using <a href=\"https://assetstore.unity.com/packages/tools/integration/steamvr-plugin-32647\">this link</a>.<br>\n<strong>Note: When upgrading from an older version, it is best to first delete the SteamVR folder in your project, and then import the package</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>The door asset that I will be using in this tutorial can be download from <a href=\"https://opengameart.org/content/wooden-squared-door\">here</a>.\n<strong>Alternatively, you can use any door to implement the same functionality.</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Due to the art model not being imported correctly, we need to make adjustments to re-align the door and its frame.\nFirst, create the door from the Prefab and place one in the scene.\n\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/inital_door-32d84e9231569c9eb83ef01805984a43-09f09.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 489px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 100.61349693251533%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"Door needs re-alignment\"\n        title=\"Door needs realignment\"\n        src=\"/static/inital_door-32d84e9231569c9eb83ef01805984a43-09f09.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/inital_door-32d84e9231569c9eb83ef01805984a43-8ae69.jpg 200w,\n/static/inital_door-32d84e9231569c9eb83ef01805984a43-4304d.jpg 400w,\n/static/inital_door-32d84e9231569c9eb83ef01805984a43-09f09.jpg 489w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 489px) 100vw, 489px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p>To perform the realignment, break the prefab by moving HingesWings_Movable out of the WoodenSquaredDoor prefab. So that your scene hierarchy looks like the one below,</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/break_prefab-1b11f5ccdd95311166c7fe7557d06fb3-ce3e0.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 261px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 39.46360153256705%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"Break Prefab\"\n        title=\"Separated parts\"\n        src=\"/static/break_prefab-1b11f5ccdd95311166c7fe7557d06fb3-ce3e0.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/break_prefab-1b11f5ccdd95311166c7fe7557d06fb3-ec6d4.jpg 200w,\n/static/break_prefab-1b11f5ccdd95311166c7fe7557d06fb3-ce3e0.jpg 261w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 261px) 100vw, 261px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<ol start=\"4\">\n<li>Create a empty gameobject and align it to the door’s hinges (pivot point). Now make the gameobject the parent of HingesWing_Movable.<br>\n<strong>Note: My empty gameobject is ‘Door’.</strong></li>\n</ol>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/door_hierarchy-a8d6dd0273db82a6434a01ce716a85d3-26377.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 273px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 25.274725274725274%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"Door rotation\"\n        title=\"Gameobject Door as parent\"\n        src=\"/static/door_hierarchy-a8d6dd0273db82a6434a01ce716a85d3-26377.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/door_hierarchy-a8d6dd0273db82a6434a01ce716a85d3-7e058.jpg 200w,\n/static/door_hierarchy-a8d6dd0273db82a6434a01ce716a85d3-26377.jpg 273w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 273px) 100vw, 273px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/pivot_point-0980ec7af5472d0e589024ec3d09fe3a-988b2.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 448px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 63.16964285714286%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"empty gameobject as pivot\"\n        title=\"Door as pivot point\"\n        src=\"/static/pivot_point-0980ec7af5472d0e589024ec3d09fe3a-988b2.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/pivot_point-0980ec7af5472d0e589024ec3d09fe3a-a9dd4.jpg 200w,\n/static/pivot_point-0980ec7af5472d0e589024ec3d09fe3a-0c1c1.jpg 400w,\n/static/pivot_point-0980ec7af5472d0e589024ec3d09fe3a-988b2.jpg 448w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 448px) 100vw, 448px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>In addition, you can test if the pivot point works by rotating it as seen below,\n<img src=\"/pivot_door-b205e9634ffae5f0dead267cc6c2518d.gif\" alt=\"Door with Pivot\"></p>\n<ol start=\"5\">\n<li>On the door knob (*_Above_Knob), add a Circular Drive script that is provided by SteamVR.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/door_knob-f20b851dd076d0054914fcc8b052b20a-142e3.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 267px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 48.68913857677903%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"Circular Drive on Door Knob\"\n        title=\"Door Handle\"\n        src=\"/static/door_knob-f20b851dd076d0054914fcc8b052b20a-142e3.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/door_knob-f20b851dd076d0054914fcc8b052b20a-8d40b.jpg 200w,\n/static/door_knob-f20b851dd076d0054914fcc8b052b20a-142e3.jpg 267w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 267px) 100vw, 267px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>Change the Axis of Rotation to Y as we want to rotate the handle up and down. Also limit the rotation the handle by setting a minimum rotation of 0° and a max rotation of 45°.\n\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/circular_drive-2064d85e4518c9971acb76b5d9c255c9-c89ff.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 350px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 72.57142857142857%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"circular_drive\"\n        title=\"Change the axis to Y\"\n        src=\"/static/circular_drive-2064d85e4518c9971acb76b5d9c255c9-c89ff.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/circular_drive-2064d85e4518c9971acb76b5d9c255c9-8d0e7.jpg 200w,\n/static/circular_drive-2064d85e4518c9971acb76b5d9c255c9-c89ff.jpg 350w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 350px) 100vw, 350px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<ol start=\"6\">\n<li>Create a mesh collider for the door handle and add it to the Circular Drive as the child collider so we can interact with it.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/mesh_collider-e1555769babd7c8c88828dd8c85e0688-a4468.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 369px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 45.25745257452575%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"Mesh Collider for Door handle\"\n        title=\"Mesh Collider for handle\"\n        src=\"/static/mesh_collider-e1555769babd7c8c88828dd8c85e0688-a4468.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/mesh_collider-e1555769babd7c8c88828dd8c85e0688-f8f4f.jpg 200w,\n/static/mesh_collider-e1555769babd7c8c88828dd8c85e0688-a4468.jpg 369w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 369px) 100vw, 369px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/child_collider-50f94627e9e3758534dd39d0951afe82-edcf1.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 352px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 32.95454545454546%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"Handle interaction\"\n        title=\"Circular Drive Child Collider\"\n        src=\"/static/child_collider-50f94627e9e3758534dd39d0951afe82-edcf1.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/child_collider-50f94627e9e3758534dd39d0951afe82-50f43.jpg 200w,\n/static/child_collider-50f94627e9e3758534dd39d0951afe82-edcf1.jpg 352w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 352px) 100vw, 352px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>Lets test it!\n<img src=\"/turning_door_knob-ab247e4e5a134586ff3b3d1f70e75d2e.gif\" alt=\"Turning door handle\"></p>\n<ol start=\"7\">\n<li>Now that our door handle works. We need to open the door after the handle is pressed down. Select ’*_Plate_Above’ and create a Sphere Collider (The Radius is up to your preference) so the user can easily open the door by pushing the handle.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/sphere_collider-47df2a42af22690ab633f9003c71340c-2b894.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 392px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 60.204081632653065%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"Sphere Collider\"\n        title=\"Sphere in Scene\"\n        src=\"/static/sphere_collider-47df2a42af22690ab633f9003c71340c-2b894.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/sphere_collider-47df2a42af22690ab633f9003c71340c-09d58.jpg 200w,\n/static/sphere_collider-47df2a42af22690ab633f9003c71340c-2b894.jpg 392w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 392px) 100vw, 392px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/sphere_collider2-b94ca12ba97f228dfe5b09b3240b320e-a4468.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 369px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 62.601626016260155%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"Sphere Collider\"\n        title=\"Sphere Collider component\"\n        src=\"/static/sphere_collider2-b94ca12ba97f228dfe5b09b3240b320e-a4468.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/sphere_collider2-b94ca12ba97f228dfe5b09b3240b320e-f8f4f.jpg 200w,\n/static/sphere_collider2-b94ca12ba97f228dfe5b09b3240b320e-a4468.jpg 369w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 369px) 100vw, 369px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<ol start=\"8\">\n<li>Create another circular drive for the main door by adding it to the empty gameobject (Door). Also add the sphere collider as the child collider and limit the rotation of the door by 0° - 90°.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/circular_drive2-0901bfd986627d63838afde1e58f37b8-5cf84.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 368px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 41.30434782608695%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"Door Handling\"\n        title=\"Interaction with door using Sphere Collider\"\n        src=\"/static/circular_drive2-0901bfd986627d63838afde1e58f37b8-5cf84.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/circular_drive2-0901bfd986627d63838afde1e58f37b8-22c8a.jpg 200w,\n/static/circular_drive2-0901bfd986627d63838afde1e58f37b8-5cf84.jpg 368w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 368px) 100vw, 368px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<ol start=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p>Now we have to make apply the phyiscs of how a door handle works. We can do this by initial disabling the Sphere Collider and only enable once the handle is rotated. Therefore, the door can only be opened after the handle is pushed down. To do this:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Disable the Sphere Collider</li>\n<li>Under max angle of the Circular Drive script (attached to Knob), we can add a function at runtime to enable the Sphere Collider whenever the max rotation is reached.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/enabled_sphere_collider-3707ceaf466c8002d84381be0e3f2034-10b0e.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 349px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 40.40114613180516%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"Enabling Sphere Collider\"\n        title=\"Enable Sphere Collider\"\n        src=\"/static/enabled_sphere_collider-3707ceaf466c8002d84381be0e3f2034-10b0e.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/enabled_sphere_collider-3707ceaf466c8002d84381be0e3f2034-8edab.jpg 200w,\n/static/enabled_sphere_collider-3707ceaf466c8002d84381be0e3f2034-10b0e.jpg 349w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 349px) 100vw, 349px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<ul>\n<li>Likewise, we can disable the mesh collider of the handle whenever the door is open (handle at 45°). Therefore the door has to be closed before the handle can return to its initial position.  </li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/disable_mesh_collider-ab870e12d9bac93ea34e8fe01dd78d21-639d0.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 353px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 46.74220963172805%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"Disabling Mesh Collider\"\n        title=\"Disable mesh collider\"\n        src=\"/static/disable_mesh_collider-ab870e12d9bac93ea34e8fe01dd78d21-639d0.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/disable_mesh_collider-ab870e12d9bac93ea34e8fe01dd78d21-3cc31.jpg 200w,\n/static/disable_mesh_collider-ab870e12d9bac93ea34e8fe01dd78d21-639d0.jpg 353w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 353px) 100vw, 353px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<ul>\n<li>Lastly, remember to enable the mesh collider whenever the door reaches back its initial position (0°) so the user can open the door again.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/door_initial_position-5365b0533d49d79df447fae1a351eef9-1ce7b.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 355px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 40.845070422535215%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"Enabling Mesh Collider\"\n        title=\"Enabling mesh collider when door is closed\"\n        src=\"/static/door_initial_position-5365b0533d49d79df447fae1a351eef9-1ce7b.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/door_initial_position-5365b0533d49d79df447fae1a351eef9-5af2f.jpg 200w,\n/static/door_initial_position-5365b0533d49d79df447fae1a351eef9-1ce7b.jpg 355w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 355px) 100vw, 355px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h3>All done</h3>\n<p>Notice that we are only able to open the door when the handle has its reached its maximum rotation of 45°. And in order to bring back the handle to its initial position (0°), we need to close the door.</p>\n<p><img src=\"/handling-12f940fd97a4e950099d0ca4dd2d585f.gif\" alt=\"Opening a door\"></p>\n<p>Credits to Unity3d College</p>","fields":{"slug":"/Creating an advanced door/","prefix":"2019-02-25"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Creating an advanced door using SteamVR Circular Drive","summary":"Creating a realistic door that only opens when the user turns the handle","author":"oliver cheok","category":"Tutorial","cover":{"childImageSharp":{"resize":{"src":"/static/cover-7ef42271918f1dcd8af613320f72f444-ada8c.jpg"}}}}},"authornote":{"id":"a1c1d9b1-9552-5af4-8afa-1cb0221135c5","html":"<p><strong>Oliver Cheok</strong> I’m a business consultant turned software engineer who loves Virtual Reality (VR). My latest project is a high immersion game that lets Users build their own contraptions to get a ball from one point to another without it touching the floor. Right now, I am working on improving my 3D Modelling skills to use my passion for VR to build personalised experiences for people.</p>"},"site":{"siteMetadata":{"facebook":{"appId":""}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/Creating an advanced door/","prev":{"id":"3607d75e-1df1-5aba-8f4b-7d4e185a2ddc","fields":{"slug":"/Custom Hands Part 1/","prefix":"2019-02-13","source":"posts"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Creating your own hand models","summary":"A quick guide to using your own hand models and creating custom hand poses using SteamVR Skeleton Poser System","category":"Tutorial"}},"next":{"id":"64a61b2a-5886-5d2e-b5b1-92ecdb073549","fields":{"slug":"/Poker Simulation/","prefix":"2019-03-12","source":"posts"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Poker Simulation","summary":"A game on emotions!","category":"Project"}},"source":"posts"}}